98 square meters.

262
00:22:46,225 --> 00:22:48,305
-Two bedrooms, two bathrooms.
-Okay.

263
00:22:48,385 --> 00:22:51,225
-I'll send it to you.
-Thank you.

264
00:22:54,985 --> 00:22:55,865
Here.

265
00:22:57,265 --> 00:22:59,825
He wants the entrance area
to feel open and airy.

266
00:22:59,905 --> 00:23:02,785
The kitchen will be next to the balcony.

267
00:23:02,865 --> 00:23:03,785
Got it.

268
00:23:04,505 --> 00:23:07,105
But first,
should we order something to eat?

269
00:23:07,905 --> 00:23:09,025
What would you like?

270
00:23:10,945 --> 00:23:12,505
Anything is fine. You can choose.

271
00:23:12,585 --> 00:23:15,225
This place is famous for many dishes.

272
00:23:17,545 --> 00:23:19,385
-Excuse me.
-Yes, sir.

273
00:23:23,785 --> 00:23:27,025
I'll have the sour curry sea bass set.

274
00:23:27,105 --> 00:23:27,945
-Yes.
-Hey.

275
00:23:28,025 --> 00:23:28,945
Thank you.

276
00:23:29,025 --> 00:23:33,305
Come on. Their shrimp pesto spaghetti

277
00:23:33,385 --> 00:23:37,625
is so famous.
I spent all day finding this place.

278
00:23:42,225 --> 00:23:44,465
I mean, for my friend.

279
00:23:47,825 --> 00:23:51,745
Then you go ahead and order.
I can eat anything.

280
00:23:51,825 --> 00:23:52,745
Okay.

281
00:23:53,385 --> 00:23:54,345
‎Excuse me.

282
00:23:54,425 --> 00:23:57,625
Shrimp pesto spaghetti,

283
00:23:57,705 --> 00:24:00,505
seafood spaghetti,

284
00:24:01,145 --> 00:24:03,425
Caesar salad,

285
00:24:05,025 --> 00:24:08,585
creamy corn salad.

286
00:24:35,705 --> 00:24:39,705
Oh, are you already full? You barely ate.

287
00:24:40,505 --> 00:24:44,785
Yes, I don't usually eat much for dinner.
Please go ahead.

288
00:24:45,305 --> 00:24:48,985
What about dessert?
Their cake is really good.

289
00:24:50,105 --> 00:24:51,105
No, thank you.

290
00:25:05,825 --> 00:25:07,225
Yes, Oon?

291
00:25:07,305 --> 00:25:09,625
Fun, are you still working?

292
00:25:09,705 --> 00:25:12,385
Yes, but I'm almost done.

293
00:25:14,705 --> 00:25:16,585
<i>Do you still have chocolate lava cake?</i>

294
00:25:18,025 --> 00:25:19,665
Two, please.

295
00:25:19,745 --> 00:25:23,265
Fun, I already ordered
your favorite chocolate cake for you.

296
00:25:26,745 --> 00:25:29,505
Sorry, you're on the phone.

297
00:25:31,345 --> 00:25:34,945
Our chocolate lava cake
is very popular among couples.

298
00:25:35,825 --> 00:25:37,105
<i>Thank you.</i>

299
00:25:41,785 --> 00:25:43,305
I've gotta go, Oon.

300
00:25:44,665 --> 00:25:45,705
Alright.

301
00:25:53,425 --> 00:25:54,985
So,

302
00:25:55,545 --> 00:25:59,145
next to the smaller bedroom,
there's a storage room.

303
00:25:59,225 --> 00:26:03,865
My friend is wondering if he should
knock down the wall to expand the space.

304
00:26:10,145 --> 00:26:14,185
That could work.
It would make the room feel bigger.

305
00:26:15,145 --> 00:26:19,865
Is he strict about feng shui?

306
00:26:20,545 --> 00:26:23,065
I don't think so.

307
00:26:23,825 --> 00:26:25,305
He believes

308
00:26:26,145 --> 00:26:29,865
that as long as you stay ahead
of your competitors, you win.

309
00:26:33,665 --> 00:26:35,385
No need to believe in things like that.

310
00:26:42,505 --> 00:26:43,545
I see.

311
00:26:46,785 --> 00:26:50,105
Please pack these to go.
And the bill as well.

312
00:26:50,185 --> 00:26:51,025
Yes.

313
00:26:51,625 --> 00:26:54,665
Krit, you can take the cakes home.

314
00:26:54,745 --> 00:26:56,705
I don't like chocolate cake.

315
00:26:58,985 --> 00:27:03,505
I'll pay for this meal.
I can reimburse it as a client expense.

316
00:27:04,785 --> 00:27:06,065
I'll take care of it.

317
00:27:06,145 --> 00:27:07,545
It's okay.

318
00:27:07,625 --> 00:27:11,585
Trust me. It's a small thing.
Don't make it a big deal.

319
00:27:17,065 --> 00:27:18,585
Come on. Let me help carry it.

320
00:27:18,665 --> 00:27:20,505
It's okay. I can carry it myself.

321
00:27:21,505 --> 00:27:23,665
After this, are you heading somewhere?

322
00:27:23,745 --> 00:27:25,585
Wanna walk
around the avenue next door with me?

323
00:27:26,145 --> 00:27:28,025
I've been there before.
There's not much there.

324
00:27:36,505 --> 00:27:37,745
I'm sorry.

325
00:27:38,665 --> 00:27:40,065
Where were you going? Be careful.

326
00:27:40,945 --> 00:27:44,665
Krit, I'm okay. It's okay.

327
00:27:46,665 --> 00:27:47,945
Krit.

328
00:27:49,425 --> 00:27:51,385
Let's go.

329
00:28:32,025 --> 00:28:33,665
I'm so tired.

330
00:28:34,825 --> 00:28:37,225
Well, you were working late.

331
00:28:39,065 --> 00:28:42,265
If it were just work,
I wouldn't be this tired.

332
00:28:44,865 --> 00:28:46,625
Did he make you uncomfortable?

333
00:28:47,505 --> 00:28:50,465
If so, just turn the job down.
You don't have to do it.

334
00:28:55,345 --> 00:28:56,625
It's okay.

335
00:28:56,705 --> 00:28:59,785
I already accepted it for the company.
I need to finish it.

336
00:29:01,345 --> 00:29:02,785
I can handle it.

337
00:29:03,345 --> 00:29:07,745
Fun, I think that Krit guy is strange.

338
00:29:08,385 --> 00:29:10,825
It feels like
he's trying to make us fight.

339
00:29:16,505 --> 00:29:18,065
Don't worry.

340
00:29:20,025 --> 00:29:21,945
I don't feel anything for him.

341
00:29:23,585 --> 00:29:25,825
He's just a childhood friend.

342
00:29:28,585 --> 00:29:30,945
I'll never feel anything for him.

343
00:29:32,065 --> 00:29:33,105
Never.

344
00:29:37,745 --> 00:29:40,225
Because I love someone beautiful.

345
00:29:41,345 --> 00:29:44,865
Especially the beautiful person
right in front of me,

346
00:29:46,105 --> 00:29:47,065
the one I love the most.

347
00:31:18,745 --> 00:31:21,105
You started it and didn't finish it.

348
00:31:52,225 --> 00:31:53,585
Good night.

349
00:33:05,385 --> 00:33:06,545
Fun.

350
00:33:11,905 --> 00:33:17,105
Are you okay? Why do you look so pale?

351
00:33:20,745 --> 00:33:22,505
My stomach hurts.

352
00:33:24,425 --> 00:33:25,985
Are you getting your period?

353
00:33:27,745 --> 00:33:28,705
Yes.

354
00:33:34,865 --> 00:33:37,425
I'm running late.
I'll get up and make you breakfast first.

355
00:33:37,505 --> 00:33:40,425
No, don't. Just lie down.

356
00:33:41,785 --> 00:33:42,985
Trust me.

357
00:33:44,345 --> 00:33:46,265
Don't get up. Just rest.

358
00:33:50,065 --> 00:33:52,825
It's okay. Just rest.

359
00:34:23,145 --> 00:34:24,385
Fun.

360
00:34:25,905 --> 00:34:26,985
Fun.

361
00:34:33,505 --> 00:34:35,705
I made porridge,

362
00:34:35,784 --> 00:34:38,465
and I brought you
painkillers and a hot water bag.

363
00:34:38,545 --> 00:34:40,145
Can you get up and eat?

364
00:34:43,065 --> 00:34:48,105
I don't feel like eating.
Can I sleep a bit more?

365
00:34:49,505 --> 00:34:50,865
Of course.

366
00:34:52,185 --> 00:34:55,625
But when you wake up, make sure
you eat and take your medicine, okay?

367
00:34:57,465 --> 00:34:58,505
Okay.

368
00:35:03,265 --> 00:35:05,705
Here, use the hot water bag first.

369
00:35:08,145 --> 00:35:09,585
Thank you.

370
00:35:11,945 --> 00:35:14,305
I'll head to work now.

371
00:35:15,225 --> 00:35:18,745
But if you need anything, call me anytime.

372
00:35:20,705 --> 00:35:22,025
Okay.

373
00:35:52,225 --> 00:35:53,065
Hey, buddy.

374
00:35:53,145 --> 00:35:55,305
It's noon. Let's go eat.

375
00:35:55,385 --> 00:35:57,145
Okay, give me a sec.

376
00:35:58,145 --> 00:36:01,945
Fifa, perfect timing. Help me with this.

377
00:36:02,865 --> 00:36:04,465
Is this one good?

378
00:36:04,545 --> 00:36:08,705
Don't forget to list this out.

379
00:36:09,425 --> 00:36:12,785
OON-OON

380
00:36:21,825 --> 00:36:22,905
Yes, Oon?

381
00:36:22,985 --> 00:36:24,305
You're still asleep?

382
00:36:24,385 --> 00:36:26,825
It's almost noon.
Have you eaten and taken your medicine?

383
00:36:26,905 --> 00:36:29,465
I don't want to eat. My stomach hurts.

384
00:36:29,545 --> 00:36:31,905
Just eat a little,
so you can take your medicine.

385
00:36:31,985 --> 00:36:35,305
I said my stomach hurts. That's it.

386
00:36:41,225 --> 00:36:43,945
If you don't take your meds,
how is it supposed to stop hurting?

387
00:36:55,465 --> 00:36:56,305
Oon?

388
00:36:58,105 --> 00:36:59,385
How did you get here?

389
00:37:01,185 --> 00:37:02,385
Are you okay?

390
00:37:03,785 --> 00:37:04,945
Where are you going?

391
00:37:06,785 --> 00:37:07,905
The sofa.

392
00:37:25,465 --> 00:37:26,985
I took the day off.

393
00:37:31,065 --> 00:37:32,905
Have you eaten?

394
00:37:34,785 --> 00:37:36,305
Yeah,

395
00:37:36,385 --> 00:37:38,145
two bites of porridge.

396
00:37:39,665 --> 00:37:40,865
Did you take your medicine?

397
00:37:41,785 --> 00:37:42,945
I did.

398
00:37:43,745 --> 00:37:45,225
Are you hungry?

399
00:37:47,225 --> 00:37:48,745
No.

400
00:37:49,625 --> 00:37:52,345
-I don't feel like eating.
-Okay.

401
00:37:56,025 --> 00:37:56,945
Come here.

402
00:38:16,705 --> 00:38:18,225
What's that smell?

403
00:38:24,185 --> 00:38:26,745
There's corn som tam, bamboo shoot soup,

404
00:38:26,825 --> 00:38:28,745
grilled pork neck and mushroom soup.

405
00:38:28,825 --> 00:38:31,265
I told you I don't want to eat.

406
00:38:32,065 --> 00:38:36,345
Just a little, okay? I wasn't sure
what you'd feel like eating,

407
00:38:36,425 --> 00:38:41,065
so I got both versions,
with and without fermented fish sauce.

408
00:38:41,145 --> 00:38:42,185
Just try a bit, okay?

409
00:38:47,545 --> 00:38:49,625
-Here.
-Thank you.

410
00:38:56,105 --> 00:38:58,025
This one doesn't have
fermented fish sauce.

411
00:39:00,705 --> 00:39:02,705
Want to try the one that does?

412
00:40:14,985 --> 00:40:17,145
Oon, wake up.

413
00:40:18,065 --> 00:40:20,465
Oon, Oon.

414
00:40:22,105 --> 00:40:24,705
Oon, wake up.

415
00:40:31,465 --> 00:40:33,385
Are you sick?

416
00:40:34,105 --> 00:40:38,145
My stomach hurts.
My period came last night.

417
00:40:39,465 --> 00:40:41,705
Oh, right,

418
00:40:41,785 --> 00:40:44,265
yours comes after mine.

419
00:40:46,145 --> 00:40:47,945
Good thing today's Saturday.

420
00:40:48,945 --> 00:40:50,985
Are you feeling better now?

421
00:40:51,905 --> 00:40:53,145
Yeah, I'm feeling better.

422
00:40:54,625 --> 00:40:57,985
Then you rest.
I'll go prepare food for you.

423
00:40:59,385 --> 00:41:00,665
Thank you.

424
00:41:12,265 --> 00:41:14,465
Fun, my stomach hurts.

425
00:41:14,545 --> 00:41:16,785
Okay, I won't tease you anymore.

426
00:41:44,545 --> 00:41:46,345
That's all?

427
00:41:47,065 --> 00:41:48,705
Yes. That's all.

428
00:41:51,145 --> 00:41:54,225
What about bamboo shoot soup?

429
00:41:55,905 --> 00:41:57,665
I want something spicy.

430
00:41:58,865 --> 00:42:01,185
Who eats fermented food
during their period?

431
00:42:02,305 --> 00:42:03,945
You ate it yesterday.

432
00:42:04,785 --> 00:42:06,945
Well, you bought it, so I had to eat it.

433
00:42:07,025 --> 00:42:08,465
Otherwise, it would've gone to waste.

434
00:42:09,785 --> 00:42:11,625
Look, everything here is good for you.

435
00:42:11,705 --> 00:42:13,745
Porridge for energy,

436
00:42:13,825 --> 00:42:17,785
ginger tea for inflammation,
painkillers for pain relief.

437
00:42:17,865 --> 00:42:21,345
And if that's not enough,
there's the hot water bag.

438
00:42:25,265 --> 00:42:28,145
Come on, hurry up and eat,
so you can take your medicine.

439
00:42:29,505 --> 00:42:31,665
Double standards.

440
00:42:43,305 --> 00:42:46,385
If you want something spicy,
I'll prepare it for your next meal.

441
00:42:48,745 --> 00:42:50,665
But no bamboo shoot soup.

442
00:42:52,345 --> 00:42:55,465
-Or are you not eating?
-I'll eat.

443
00:42:57,665 --> 00:42:59,345
No bamboo shoot soup.

444
00:43:11,625 --> 00:43:15,425
Oon,
the complex site got approved already.

445
00:43:15,505 --> 00:43:17,105
That was fast, start to finish.

446
00:43:18,185 --> 00:43:19,545
That's true.

447
00:43:22,545 --> 00:43:27,025
Hey, I heard this client
specifically requested you.

448
00:43:29,345 --> 00:43:31,185
I've never even met them.

449
00:43:31,865 --> 00:43:34,665
What do you mean?
It's your girlfriend's friend.

450
00:43:35,945 --> 00:43:39,105
Oh, and in two days, we have to send
everything to the consultant.

451
00:43:39,185 --> 00:43:43,385
Please gather all the documents and have
a messenger deliver them to their office.

452
00:43:43,465 --> 00:43:47,065
Nu, Nat got into an accident yesterday.
He's in the hospital.

453
00:43:47,145 --> 00:43:49,065
We'll probably need an external messenger.

454
00:43:50,665 --> 00:43:51,665
Oh, right.

455
00:43:54,785 --> 00:43:57,345
It's okay, I'll deliver them myself.

456
00:43:58,545 --> 00:43:59,385
Sounds good.

457
00:44:22,665 --> 00:44:23,625
Come in.

458
00:44:33,945 --> 00:44:34,785
Ms. Aioon.

459
00:44:38,065 --> 00:44:38,945
Please come in.

460
00:44:42,625 --> 00:44:44,025
-Hello.
-Hello.

461
00:44:45,305 --> 00:44:46,345
These are the documents.

462
00:44:46,425 --> 00:44:47,425
Please have a seat.

463
00:44:49,025 --> 00:44:52,985
Honestly, you could've just sent
these with a messenger.

464
00:44:53,625 --> 00:44:55,545
I happened to be nearby,

465
00:44:55,625 --> 00:44:59,065
so I thought I'd drop them off myself,
just in case anything needed fixing.

466
00:45:00,585 --> 00:45:02,905
There shouldn't be any issues.
I've reviewed everything.

467
00:45:02,985 --> 00:45:05,865
Your work is very thorough.
It's impressive.

468
00:45:06,585 --> 00:45:07,545
Thank you.

469
00:45:09,785 --> 00:45:10,625
Come in.

470
00:45:29,425 --> 00:45:31,825
Have you ever thought
about taking on projects independently?

471
00:45:34,225 --> 00:45:36,105
I have a lot of clients.

472
00:45:37,185 --> 00:45:40,425
If you join my team, I guarantee

473
00:45:40,505 --> 00:45:42,105
you'll earn a lot.

474
00:45:43,145 --> 00:45:45,105
Thank you for the offer,

475
00:45:46,185 --> 00:45:51,065
but I don't think I'm capable enough
to work with you, Mr. Kritsana.

476
00:45:52,785 --> 00:45:54,905
-Excuse me.
-Come in.

477
00:45:58,225 --> 00:45:59,145
Excuse me.

478
00:45:59,905 --> 00:46:03,185
There’s a budget document
that urgently needs your signature.

479
00:46:04,145 --> 00:46:05,025
No problem.

480
00:46:23,945 --> 00:46:25,985
-Here. Thanks.
-Yes, sir.

481
00:46:31,545 --> 00:46:35,745
I'll head out now,
so you can continue your work.

482
00:46:35,825 --> 00:46:38,225
It's fine, we can keep talking.

483
00:46:42,025 --> 00:46:46,065
If there's anything else,
please let me know.

484
00:46:46,705 --> 00:46:47,625
Sure.

485
00:46:55,065 --> 00:46:58,545
If you're ever interested in my offer,
feel free to contact me anytime.

486
00:47:18,945 --> 00:47:21,145
<i>I'm just offering you a good option,</i>

487
00:47:21,825 --> 00:47:23,345
<i>a life where you don't have to struggle.</i>

488
00:47:23,425 --> 00:47:27,985
A house, a car, anything you want,
I can give it to you.

489
00:47:28,905 --> 00:47:30,425
You don't have to leave Aioon,

490
00:47:30,505 --> 00:47:33,545
but when I call, you come.

491
00:47:37,585 --> 00:47:38,985
Oon, what's wrong?

492
00:47:39,065 --> 00:47:41,865
<i>I can't build a future for you anymore.</i>

493
00:47:41,945 --> 00:47:43,865
I've been suspended from work.

494
00:48:12,545 --> 00:48:14,945
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon

